The proposed Draft Plan of Common Element Condominium is being submitted at this time to facilitate the creation and approval of the shared common elements required for the subject lands. These elements include the private roadway, visitor parking spaces, shared landscape areas, the tot lot and amenity space, and location of the community mailboxes. It is noted that a separate

Proposal to convert the existing 6 storey, 72 unit rental apartment building into a standard condominium.

The subject lands are located at Goreway Drive at its intersection with Halliford Place near the
intersection of Goreway Drive and the Humberwest Parkway in the City of Brampton. The lands are
municipally known as 9159 Goreway Drive and are legally described as Block 1 on Plan 43M-2098 &
Block 7 on Plan 43M-2101.

The lands are within the Goreway Drive Corridor Secondary Plan which designates them Medium-High &
High Density Residential, which permits the proposed residential development. The approved site-specific
Zoning By-Law zones the lands to the R4A - Residential Apartment A zone with a number of development
standards which facilitate the approved Site Plan.

The approved Site Plan contemplates 100 condominium townhouse units situated within 7 townhouse
blocks on a 0.961hectare parcel of land with 127 parking spaces. The arrangement of private streets,
parking areas for residents and visitors, walkways, and landscaped open space are illustrated on the
approved Site Plan and Landscape Plans. The proposed Draft Plan of Standard Condominium will establish
and facilitate the standard condominium ownership of the approved development.
